Prometheus + Custom Exporter + Grafana
This is what serious production setups use.

📊 What your Grafana dashboard would show
Per-DB connection usage
% utilization (Active / MaxAllowed)
Threshold line at 280
Spike history

🟢 STEP 1: Create a Custom Exporter (Python – simple & reliable)
📄db_api_exporter.py
🟢 STEP 2: Dockerize the exporter
📄Dockerfile
🟢 STEP 3: Deploy exporter to Kubernetes
📄 db-api-exporter.yaml
🟢 STEP 4: Tell Prometheus to scrape it
📄 db-api-servicemonitor.yaml
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
| File                         | Needed?  | Why                       |
| ---------------------------- | -------  | ------------------------- |
| `db-api-exporter.yaml`       | ✅ Yes   | runs your exporter        |
| `db-api-servicemonitor.yaml` | ✅ Yes   | lets Prometheus scrape it |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ Final Architecture (clean & standard)
----------------------------------------
DB Health API
   ↓
Custom DB Exporter (K8s Pod)
   ↓   /metrics
Prometheus
   ↓
Grafana Dashboard

1️⃣ Open Prometheus UI:
kubectl port-forward -n monitoring svc/prometheus-kube-prometheus-stack-prometheus 9090
2️⃣ Go to the Graph tab:
3️⃣ Run the metric query:
db_active_connections

✅ The ONE setting you need: Legend format:
🔹 Query : db_active_connections
🔹 Legend : {{database}}
🔹 Min step : empty or auto
🔹 Format : Time series
🔹 Type : Range

